From Abel Leonard, Lafia Speaker, Nasarawa State House of Assembly, Alh Ibrahim Balarabe Abdullahi, has described the death of Hassan, the son of Governor Abdullahi Sule as a great shock, painful and colossal to the entire State. Speaker Balarabe Abdullahi, who is mourning the passing on of the one he described as a promising, humble and cherished young man, prayed God to forgive his shortcomings, grant him paradise and comfort the family. He condoled with Governor Abdullahi Sule, the State First Lady, Hajiya Silifat Abdullahi Sule, the entire family and the State at large over the great loss. Speaker Balarabe Abdullahi who described death as inevitable to every mortal that will occur whenever God so desired, urged Governor Abdullahi Sule, his family, friends and the entire citizens to see his demise as the will of God and continue to pray for the reposed of his soul. “We woke up this morning with the sad and shocking news of our dear son, Hassan, the son of his Excellency Governor Abdullahi Sule, what can we say, God Almighty is the sole giver and taker of life, this is one death too many at this time, it is very shocking, painful and colossal, may the Almighty Allah accept all his good deeds, forgive his shortcomings and grant him Aljanatul firdausi as his final abode and comfort us all” the Speaker added.